Compatibility shim for building telegraf against the rclone v1.74.3
release tag, which the go/bump step pins for CVE-2026-49980.

Telegraf v1.39.1 upstream depends on an rclone master pseudo-version
(v1.74.1-0.20260628215305-6bbc28cf02dc) that already contains the
log/slog rewrite from https://github.com/rclone/rclone/pull/8329, and
routes rclone logging into the plugin logger via fs.SetLogger. No tagged
rclone release ships fs.SetLogger yet (v1.74.3 is the newest tag), so
after pinning the release tag that call does not compile. Drop the
logging hook (same approach the previous revision of this shim used for
the removed fs.LogOutput) until an rclone release exposes fs.SetLogger.

diff --git a/plugins/outputs/remotefile/remotefile.go b/plugins/outputs/remotefile/remotefile.go
--- a/plugins/outputs/remotefile/remotefile.go
+++ b/plugins/outputs/remotefile/remotefile.go
@@ -21,7 +21,6 @@
 	"github.com/influxdata/telegraf"
 	"github.com/influxdata/telegraf/config"
 	"github.com/influxdata/telegraf/internal"
-	"github.com/influxdata/telegraf/plugins/common/slog"
 	"github.com/influxdata/telegraf/plugins/outputs"
 )

@@ -85,8 +84,5 @@
 		f.vfsopts.CacheMaxSize = fs.SizeSuffix(f.MaxCacheSize)
 	}

-	// Route rclone's internal logging through the plugin logger
-	fs.SetLogger(slog.NewLogger(f.Log).Handler())
-
 	// Setup custom template functions
 	funcs := template.FuncMap{"now": time.Now}
